latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I used to do this a lot when I didn’t have much work as an actor…it’s been a while since I’ve randomly picked up a piece and performed it. This one’s from a show called “Scenes from a marriage” 
It did something to me while I was watching this particular episode and I just wanted to give this a shot. For the people who know me; they know how and why I would connect to this particular script and the fact that I’m a complete sucker for melancholia, longing and just love in general (unrequited or otherwise) because these are the emotions that ground you and make you feel human. 
So here’s my rookie attempt at this brilliant piece of writing ✌️🎞
(Use headphones for better clarity)

latestPosts.caption:
Gurfateh Singh Pirzada (@gurfatehpirzada) bares it all for The Cosmo Centrefold—both, literally and figuratively. The 27-year-old actor talks to Cosmo India’s Deputy Editor Simi Kuriakose (@si.mi.later) about being a shy person, thriving in Mumbai, and what he looks for in a partner. 

Excerpt from the interview: 
When asked if he’s enjoying the attention since becoming THE heartthrob after Call me Bae, Pirzada responded saying that he doesn’t think he’s the heartthrob this time, but a green flag apparently. “For the longest time, people would reach out to me after watching my work, and be like, your character was so bad, but, we still loved you. So, it is refreshing to hear out-and-out good things about Neel’s [Call me Bae] character. I hope this translates into something bigger. We recently announced that Season 2 is in development, and I hope the story goes further along for Bae [Ananya Panday] and Neel...and I get a bigger reel track in the next season (laughs).”

Head to the link in bio for the full story!

latestPosts.caption: I have always been drawn to clean, effortless styles — the kind that are hard to come by. After searching high and low, finally found my match at @mangostoresindia. Can’t wait to stock up on my wardrobe essentials with the Spring Summer Collection!

It’s been a gruelling few months….non stop work, prep, working out…and then a string of injuries (LITERALLY EVERYDAY) 🫠
But here we are again…trying to get back to what I was a month ago!!! 

But hey, Life’s not too bad…so no reason to fret over anything! 👀 
Also exciting EXCITING things coming up🤞🤞🤞
